						class Item45
						{
							dataType="Object";
							class PositionInfo
							{
								position[]={14771.667,18.456381,16836.857};
								angles[]={0,5.7330227,0};
							};
							side="Empty";
							class Attributes
							{
							};
							id=3650;
							type="acex_intelitems_document";
							atlOffset=0.044067383;
							class CustomAttributes
							{
								class Attribute0
								{
									property="ace_intelitems_data";
									expression="[_this, _value] call ace_intelitems_fnc_setObjectData";
									class Value
									{
										class data
										{
											singleType="STRING";
											value="Logbook Entry – 01 November" \n "" \n "Four months in, and every day feels like borrowed time with this guest of ours. Orders are simple: guard it, and if anything happens—if there’s even a hint of a breach—use the code, open the door, and send in the guards to eliminate the threat. They’ve drilled it into us with good reason. This thing isn’t just muscle and claws; it has a way of getting into your head, slipping in like a poison you can’t shake. Last week, Thompson got too close, locked eyes with it for just a second, and he hasn’t been right since. Quiet, pale, muttering to himself… it’s like he’s still hearing its voice." \n "" \n "We’ve got soundproof walls, double-locked doors, all the firepower you can imagine, but somehow, it never feels like enough. Command insists we’re safe with protocols in place, but one wrong move and that thing could be loose. If it comes to that, we have to act fast. Don’t hesitate—containment access code is 9309.";
										};
									};
								};
								nAttributes=1;
							};
						};
